yup, very similar to what I came up with. Which basically means all we 
would really need to do is settle on trivial details such as tag and 
attribute names - I&#39;ll adopt yours since they seem entirely 
reasonable/straightforward. Perhaps some additional data at the head of 
a file to indicate which implementation and code version the data came 
from and other stuff like that. Note that the XML I posted was purely a 
NN definition - not a genome/chromosome. The distinction was necessary 
because I was using an indirect encoding.  I never got around to 
outputting genome XML but with NEAT being a direct encoding one XML 
dialect does both jobs.


